What does the final keyword do?: What is the Liskov Substitution Principle?
Prevents the class from being inherited: Any subtype can be used instead of the supertype without breaking the program
Ends a for-loop: Subclasses can force superclasses to implement a method

What does the final keyword do?: What is the purpose of the default keyword?
Ends the program: Defines a default method and its implementation in an interface
